program.name: Nurse-Family Partnership (NFP)
program.description:
Help for first-time parents. NFP partners first-time parents with a free personal nurse for regular in-home visits. This nurse can offer personal pregnancy and postpartum care and support. You will get tools and information to give your baby a healthy start. Nurses may also help you create a job and education plan.

Your nurse will support you up to your baby's second birthday. You should apply during pregnancy but may be able to enroll for up to 30 days after your baby's birth.
